<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4547274>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 1. — Distribution of giant Gehyra Gray, 1834 in the Pacific region: outlines delimit ranges of G. marginata Boulenger, 1887 (ma), G. membranacruralis King & Horner, 1989 (me), G. georgpotthasti n. sp. (ge), and G. vorax Girard, 1957 (vo); archipelagos, islands and regions with known occurrences are shaded black; arrows connect populations introduced to Polynesia (l) and the doubtful record from Norfolk Island (N) with their respective origins; grey hatched areas illustrate distribution of G. oceanica (Lesson, 1830)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4547274/files/figure.png" .

